Program: Discovery
Title: The Hubble Telescope and the first stars
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry32
Last Broadcast Date: 14 May 2002
Tracking down the first stars using Hubble space telescope. How looking backwards, and outwards can help us look back at the early universe. The starlight we get on earth is often millions of years old, now cosmologists are trying to look back and find what they call the missing piece in the story of how the universe evolved. Show less